# Config

Three layers, most specific wins: **user** (`~/.config/worktrunk/config.toml`, or
`%APPDATA%\worktrunk\config.toml`), **project** (`.config/wt.toml` at the repo
root, team-shared), and a platform **system** file. `wt config show` prints the
merged result and the system path. @wt/hook lives in the same files.

## Worktree path template

Where `wt switch` puts a new worktree:

```toml
worktree-path = "{{ repo_path }}/.worktrees/{{ branch | sanitize }}"
```

Variables: `repo_path` (absolute), `repo` (dir name), `owner` (remote owner),
`branch` (raw). Filters: `sanitize` (`/`,`\` → `-`), `sanitize_db` (lowercase +
underscores + hash), `codename(2)` (deterministic friendly name), `hash_port`
(stable per-branch port — handy for dev servers).

## Per-command defaults

```toml
[merge]
squash = true; commit = true; rebase = true; remove = true; verify = true; ff = true

[commit]
stage = "all"            # "all" | "tracked" | "none"

[remove]
delete-branch = true

[switch]
cd = true
[switch.picker]
pager = "delta --paging=never"

[step.copy-ignored]
exclude = []             # extra excludes; built-ins always apply
```

## List columns

```toml
[list]
full = false; branches = false; remotes = false
columns = ["branch", "status", "ci", "path"]
url = "http://localhost:{{ branch | hash_port }}"

[list.custom-columns.Ticket]
template = "{{ vars.ticket }}"
width = 20
priority = 9
```

Built-in columns: `branch status working-diff ahead-behind branch-diff summary
upstream ci path url commit age message`.

## LLM commit generation

```toml
[commit.generation]
command = "claude -p --model=haiku ..."   # any tool that reads a prompt, writes a msg
template = "<task>Write a commit message…</task>"
squash-template = "<task>Combined effect…</task>"
template-append = "- Explain the rationale in the body"
```

## Aliases, per-project, state

```toml
[aliases]
url = "echo http://localhost:{{ branch | hash_port }}"

[projects."github.com/user/repo"]
worktree-path = ".worktrees/{{ branch | sanitize }}"
list.full = true
merge.squash = false
```

Per-branch state (markers show in @wt/list):

```bash
wt config state vars set env=staging
wt config state marker set 🚧
wt config state cache clear
```

## Overrides without editing files

```bash
# env: kebab key → SCREAMING_SNAKE, nesting = double underscore
WORKTRUNK_WORKTREE_PATH=… WORKTRUNK_COMMIT__STAGE=all wt …

# inline TOML, per invocation
wt --config-set list.full=true list
```
